answers:
@ChrisGranade solved my problem:

It looks like your IQ# version is 0.11.2006.403, but you're trying to add version 0.11.2004.2825 of the Microsoft.Quantum.MachineLearning package. I'd suggest either downgrading IQ# to 0.11.2004.2825, or modifying the qsharp.packages.add call to use 0.11.2006.403
comments: Can you share the output of dotnet iqsharp --version at the command line, or qsharp.component_versions() from within Python? That would help us to diagnose your error much better. Thank you for your help!
@ChrisGranade Please check the edited post... I added the versions. Thanks in advance for your help.

That helps a lot, thank you! It looks like your IQ# version is 0.11.2006.403, but you're trying to add version 0.11.2004.2825 of the Microsoft.Quantum.MachineLearning package. I'd suggest either downgrading IQ# to 0.11.2004.2825, or modifying the qsharp.packages.add call to use 0.11.2006.403.
Thanks a lot @ChrisGranade! That solved my problem.
